atg.search.routing.command.SearchEngineRequest, java.io.Serializable
public class ParserOptions
extends OptionsBase

Text processing options for requests.

Optional: All

Required: None Call the backdoor method setXml(String) if you already have well-formed xml and want to override settings; or you can call the static valueOf(String).

setXml

public void setXml(java.lang.String pXml)
Method for overriding everything in this class from well-formed xml. Be careful when using this, the XML is not validated and must be correct.

The parser options will be initialized from whatever the parser finds. Ill-formed XML may result in partially initialized parser options. If you are using a parser, see fromXmlParser(atg.search.routing.utils.SearchMessageNode).

Parameters:
pXml - parser option xml
